         <c id="aspace_f7ca9fd8e925fafd0202cfb23342ee7b" level="file">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Painter Family</unittitle>
               <unitdatestructured unitdatetype="inclusive">
                  <datesingle standarddate="1900">1900</datesingle>
               </unitdatestructured>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_6c27c9cde9e047c89e0a410ed402ac0e">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The original documents were written by Thomas Painter in 1836. Included in the biographical material is information on Thomas Painter's service during the Revolutionary War, first in the militia and later in the navy. There is also significant information on his maritime career before and after the war.
The versions in this collection are manuscript copies made by his granddaughter, Alice Bartlett, in 1900. There are also some loose pages of genealogical information concerning the Painter family.
The material became part of the Sturgis family records through Philip Golden Bartlett, brother of Alice Bartlett and husband of Russell Sturgis' daughter Beatrice.</p>
            </scopecontent>
